main event: The observer sighted red and white flashing lights that traveled from east to north and was visible for a short duration.
interesting points: The witness reported feeling a heavy, oppressive feeling and a tingling sensation during the observation.
One object moved from northeast to southeast and then disappeared, while the other object remained stationary.
The sighted object was described as a round, bright light that hovered at one point, then accelerated and disappeared from view.
A private flying instructor witnessed an unidentified object in the vicinity of Vinton, Ohio on August 21, 1965.
The sighting could not have been of an aircraft according to the Project Blue Book evaluation.
sighted object: One (1) object, red and white flashing lights, round bright light
